1. Authentication Endpoints
These endpoints are part of your system app and are used for handling user authentication and token management.

Login and obtain token pair:

Path: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/auth/login/

Method: POST

Purpose: To get a new access and refresh token pair by sending user credentials.

Refresh access token:

Path: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/auth/token/refresh/

Method: POST

Purpose: To get a new access token using a valid refresh token.

Verify a token:

Path: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/auth/token/verify/

Method: POST

Purpose: To verify that a token is valid.

2. Appraisal Endpoints
These endpoints are for the core appraisal functionality in your appraisals app.

Employee self-appraisal submission:

Path: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/appraisals/self-appraisal/

Method: POST or PUT

Purpose: To create or update an employee's self-appraisal form.

Reporting manager review:

Path: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/appraisals/manager-review/<int:appraisal_id>/

Method: POST or PUT

Purpose: To submit or update a review from a reporting manager for a specific appraisal. You will need to replace <int:appraisal_id> with the actual numerical ID of the appraisal you are reviewing.

HR review:

Path: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/appraisals/hr-review/<int:appraisal_id>/

Method: POST or PUT

Purpose: To submit or update a review from an HR representative for a specific appraisal. Again, you'll need the appraisal's ID.

Final review:

Path: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/appraisals/final-review/<int:appraisal_id>/

Method: POST or PUT

Purpose: To complete the final review for an appraisal. You must provide the correct appraisal ID.